Introduction of requirements set for conducting scientific research, use of scientific literature and databases in research, and characteristics, structure and writing conventions of students' research papers. The main focus is on how to apply specialist knowledge in writing of a bachelor's thesis or examination paper, and to provide required scientific-methodological recommendations. At seminars, first drafts of bachelor's theses will be discussed, and detailed recommendations will be given to complete research work.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The student has the skills to write scientific research papers and the student gets support in the bachelor's thesis / exam preparation process.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student:  - understands basic concepts of research work and the system approach, and peculiarities of social research;  - designs research work;  - analyses techniques for conducting different types of research work;  - implements the use of sources and in-text referencing techniques;  - explains how to write a research paper according to the effective academic writing guidelines;  - assesses the knowledge of theory acquired during research work.
